’ђђЪмTitle: This week in Nu #5
Path: This week in Nu #5
Content:
This week we released 0.3.0! This is the first release on a new 3-week release cycle.
Most of our energy was focused on getting the release out and as part of the release, which meant fixing lots of issues:
landaire made ctrl-c behavior configurable (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/706] #706
)
svartalf fixed an issue with detecting disks in macOS (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/700] #700
)
andrasio fixed a few issues with plugins (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/697] #697
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/698] #698
)
est31 moved us one more step closer to building on stable (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/713] #731
)
pka fixed an issue when trying to build without crossterm support (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/704] #704
)
piotrek-szczygiel fixed usage info for the echo command (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/705] #705
)
BradyBromly made some improvements to the README (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/720] #720
)
Also big thanks to our issue reporters: lienke, cHolzberger, futile, dbarnett, SafariMonkey, jonmast, eklmv, sorrell, Nalleyer, and rirze.
